      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(openai): honor streamed tool calls with stop finish",
        "body": "Fixes #88791.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Preserve streamed Chat Completions `tool_calls` even when an OpenAI-compatible provider ends the stream with `finish_reason: stop`, but only for silent turns with no visible assistant text.\n- Keep the existing safety guard that strips spurious stop-finished tool calls when the reply already contains visible text.\n- Add focused regressions for silent stop-plus-tool-calls, empty `tool_calls`, and visible-text spurious tool calls.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: A streamed OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions response can contain structured `tool_calls` but finish with `finish_reason: stop`. Before this patch OpenClaw mapped the terminal reason to `stop` and stripped the tool-call blocks, leaving the turn with no executable tool call.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw-88791`, branch `fix/openai-stop-tool-calls-88791`, commit `9a4ce38916`.\n\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts -- -t \"promotes stop completions with structured tool calls|strips tool call blocks when provider signals finish_reason stop|resets stopReason to stop\"\ngit log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  3 passed | 214 skipped (217)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 4.08s\n9a4ce38916 Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> fix(openai): honor streamed tool calls with stop finish\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The silent mocked provider stream with `tool_calls` plus final `finish_reason: stop` now ends with `stopReason: \"toolUse\"` and retains the parsed `toolCall` block. The visible-text spurious-tool-call stream still ends with `stopReason: \"stop\"` and strips the tool call, preserving the existing provider-safety behavior.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not run against the reporter's live vLLM/Qwen deployment; the regression uses a source-level Chat Completions stream matching the reported provider shape.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Maintainer can modify: enabled.\n",
